    "## 2. Dataset file paths\n",
    "\n",
    "`dataset_paths` lists the feather files for the two monitoring sites (St. Ebbes and High St.).\n",
    "Each site has three files: the ratified record, the 2021 extension, and a transients update.\n",
    "`DATA_DIR` is the folder holding them — leave it as `\"\"` when the files sit next to the notebook.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d67b3ef4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Load the raw data\n",
    "\n",
    "`load_site(...)` reads the three feather files for one site and stacks them into a single table indexed by `[tag, rec]` (`tag` = sensor id, `rec` = timestamp). It also:\n",
    "- downcasts `float64 → float32` to save memory, and\n",
    "- builds `pm25_ugg_combo`, a combined PM₂.₅ column where negative readings are treated as missing.\n",
    "\n",
    "The result is two tables: `sebbes_raw` and `highs_raw`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "16b8d229",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "St. Ebbes: (202170, 96)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sebbes_files = [\n",
    "    \"sebbes_train_536_s15_ratified.ftr\",\n",
    "    \"sebbes_train_536_s15_ratified+2021.ftr\",\n",
    "    \"sebbes_train_s15+2021_oct_update_transients_may22.ftr\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_site(ftr_files):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Read and stack feather files, indexed by [tag, rec]; downcast float64 -> float32.\"\"\"\n",
    "    frames = []\n",
    "    for fname in ftr_files:\n",
    "        df = pd.read_feather(fname).set_index([\"tag\", \"rec\"]).sort_index()\n",
    "        f64 = df.select_dtypes(np.float64).columns\n",
    "        df[f64] = df[f64].astype(np.float32)\n",
    "        frames.append(df)\n",
    "    return pd.concat(frames)\n",
    "\n",
    "sebbes_raw = load_site(sebbes_files)\n",
    "print(\"St. Ebbes:\", sebbes_raw.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1e5d41a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Keep only the columns we need\n",
    "\n",
    "`keep_cols` is the short list of raw signals used downstream:\n",
    "- `val.mtf1/3/5/7` — sensor optical channels, `val.sfr` — sample flow, `val.hmd` — humidity, `val.tmp` — temperature,\n",
    "- `val.pm2p5_1_c1` — the sensor's own PM₂.₅ estimate,\n",
    "- `pm25_ugg_s` — **reference PM₂.₅ (the target we calibrate to)**, plus `pm25_ugg_h` and `pm25_ugg_combo`.\n",
    "\n",
    "`trim(...)` drops everything else and only keeps columns that actually exist, so the cell won't crash if one is absent.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "8a0b9a29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Trimmed: (202170, 11)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "keep_cols = [\n",
    "    \"val.mtf1\", \"val.mtf5\", \"val.mtf3\", \"val.mtf7\",\n",
    "    \"val.sfr\", \"val.hmd\", \"val.tmp\",\n",
    "    \"val.pm2p5_1_c1\",\n",
    "    \"pm25_ugg_s\",     # reference PM2.5 (TARGET)\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "def trim(df):\n",
    "    df = df.reset_index()\n",
    "    cols = [\"tag\", \"rec\"] + [c for c in keep_cols if c in df.columns]\n",
    "    return df[cols].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "sebbes_trim = trim(sebbes_raw)\n",
    "print(\"Trimmed:\", sebbes_trim.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "82247103",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Feature-engineering helpers\n",
    "\n",
    "Two small functions add features that help the LSTM:\n",
    "- `pct_change_features(df)` — adds the 1-step (`pc15_`) and 2-step (`pc30_`) percent change of every numeric column, capturing short-term trends (data is at 15-min resolution).\n",
    "- `time_flags(df)` — adds `hour`, `day` (day-of-week) and a `rushhour` flag (`1` = morning peak, `2` = evening peak, `0` otherwise).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d7629ae6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pct_change_features(df):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Add 1-step (pc15_) and 2-step (pc30_) percent change of every numeric column.\"\"\"\n",
    "    num  = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])\n",
    "    pc15 = num.pct_change(periods=1).add_prefix(\"pc15_\")\n",
    "    pc30 = num.pct_change(periods=2).add_prefix(\"pc30_\")\n",
    "    return pd.concat([df, pc15, pc30], axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "def time_flags(df):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Add hour, day-of-week and a rush-hour flag (1 = morning peak, 2 = evening peak).\"\"\"\n",
    "    rec = df.index.get_level_values(\"rec\")\n",
    "    df[\"hour\"] = rec.hour\n",
    "    df[\"day\"]  = rec.dayofweek\n",
    "    df[\"rushhour\"] = 0\n",
    "    df.loc[(rec.time >= dt.time(7, 30)) & (rec.time < dt.time(9, 30)) & (rec.dayofweek < 5), \"rushhour\"] = 1\n",
    "    df.loc[(rec.time >= dt.time(16, 0)) & (rec.time < dt.time(18, 0)) & (rec.dayofweek < 5), \"rushhour\"] = 2\n",
    "    df[\"rushhour\"] = df[\"rushhour\"].astype(np.int32)\n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5f6c81d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Apply feature engineering per sensor\n",
    "\n",
    "`build_features(...)` runs the two helpers **separately for each sensor (`tag`)** so percent-change values never leak across sensors, then stacks the results back together.\n",
    "Produces `sebbes_features` and `highs_features`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "8c590c4e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Features: (202170, 30)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def build_features(df_trim):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Run percent-change and time features for each sensor (tag) separately, then stack.\"\"\"\n",
    "    df_trim = df_trim.set_index([\"tag\", \"rec\"])\n",
    "    out = []\n",
    "    for tag in df_trim.index.get_level_values(\"tag\").unique():\n",
    "        d = df_trim.loc[tag].copy()\n",
    "        d[\"tag\"] = tag\n",
    "        d = d.reset_index().set_index([\"tag\", \"rec\"])\n",
    "        d = pct_change_features(d)\n",
    "        d = time_flags(d)\n",
    "        out.append(d)\n",
    "    return pd.concat(out).sort_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "sebbes_features = build_features(sebbes_trim)\n",
    "print(\"Features:\", sebbes_features.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e4c0463c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Build the model-ready table\n",
    "\n",
    "`build_model_table(...)` takes the per-site features, slices them to a date window, and adds the final feature set:\n",
    "- **calendar / seasonal** terms (`hour`, `day`, `month`, `season`) plus their sine/cosine encodings so the model sees them as cyclical,\n",
    "- **interaction terms** (e.g. `mtf3_tmp_ratio`, `sfr_hmd_product`).\n",
    "\n",
    "It then keeps a fixed column list, replaces infinities with `NaN`, and drops bad rows. The output is a clean numeric table indexed by `[tag, rec]`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "06dc4c88",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def build_model_table(feature_frames, start, end):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Slice to a date window, add calendar/seasonal/interaction features,\n",
    "    keep a fixed column list, drop bad rows. Indexed by [tag, rec].\"\"\"\n",
    "    start = pd.to_datetime(start, utc=True)\n",
    "    end   = pd.to_datetime(end,   utc=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # slice each frame on the 'rec' timestamp index (no .query -> no scope issue)\n",
    "    frames = []\n",
    "    for df in feature_frames:\n",
    "        rec = df.index.get_level_values(\"rec\")\n",
    "        frames.append(df[(rec >= start) & (rec < end)])\n",
    "    df = pd.concat(frames).sort_index()\n",
    "    df = df[~df.index.duplicated()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    rec = df.index.get_level_values(\"rec\")\n",
    "    df[\"hour\"] = rec.hour\n",
    "    df[\"day\"]  = rec.dayofweek\n",
    "    df[\"rushhour\"] = 0\n",
    "    df.loc[(rec.time >= dt.time(7, 30)) & (rec.time < dt.time(9, 30)) & (rec.dayofweek < 5), \"rushhour\"] = 1\n",
    "    df.loc[(rec.time >= dt.time(16, 0)) & (rec.time < dt.time(18, 0)) & (rec.dayofweek < 5), \"rushhour\"] = 2\n",
    "    df[\"rushhour\"] = df[\"rushhour\"].astype(np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "    df[\"hour_sin\"]   = np.sin(2*np.pi*df[\"hour\"]/24);    df[\"hour_cos\"]   = np.cos(2*np.pi*df[\"hour\"]/24)\n",
    "    df[\"day_sin\"]    = np.sin(2*np.pi*df[\"day\"]/7);      df[\"day_cos\"]    = np.cos(2*np.pi*df[\"day\"]/7)\n",
    "    df[\"month\"]      = rec.month\n",
    "    df[\"season\"]     = df[\"month\"] % 12 // 3\n",
    "    df[\"month_sin\"]  = np.sin(2*np.pi*df[\"month\"]/12);   df[\"month_cos\"]  = np.cos(2*np.pi*df[\"month\"]/12)\n",
    "    df[\"season_sin\"] = np.sin(2*np.pi*df[\"season\"]/4);   df[\"season_cos\"] = np.cos(2*np.pi*df[\"season\"]/4)\n",
    "\n",
    "    df[\"mtf3_tmp_ratio\"]   = df[\"val.mtf3\"] / (df[\"val.tmp\"] + 1e-3)\n",
    "    df[\"sfr_hmd_ratio\"]    = df[\"val.sfr\"]  / (df[\"val.hmd\"] + 1e-3)\n",
    "    df[\"mtf3_tmp_product\"] = df[\"val.mtf3\"] * df[\"val.tmp\"]\n",
    "    df[\"sfr_hmd_product\"]  = df[\"val.sfr\"]  * df[\"val.hmd\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "    final_columns = [\n",
    "        \"val.mtf1\", \"val.mtf5\", \"val.mtf3\", \"val.mtf7\", \"val.sfr\", \"val.hmd\", \"val.tmp\",\n",
    "        \"pc15_val.mtf1\", \"pc15_val.mtf5\", \"pc15_val.mtf3\", \"pc15_val.mtf7\",\n",
    "        \"pc15_val.sfr\", \"pc15_val.hmd\", \"pc15_val.tmp\",\n",
    "        \"pc30_val.mtf1\", \"pc30_val.mtf5\", \"pc30_val.mtf3\", \"pc30_val.mtf7\",\n",
    "        \"pc30_val.sfr\", \"pc30_val.hmd\", \"pc30_val.tmp\",\n",
    "        \"hour\", \"day\", \"rushhour\",\n",
    "        \"pm25_ugg_s\",                       # TARGET\n",
    "        \"val.pm2p5_1_c1\", \"pc15_val.pm2p5_1_c1\", \"pc30_val.pm2p5_1_c1\",\n",
    "        \"hour_sin\", \"hour_cos\", \"day_sin\", \"day_cos\",\n",
    "        \"month_sin\", \"month_cos\", \"season_sin\", \"season_cos\",\n",
    "        \"mtf3_tmp_ratio\", \"sfr_hmd_ratio\", \"mtf3_tmp_product\", \"sfr_hmd_product\",\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    cols = [c for c in final_columns if c in df.columns]\n",
    "    df = df[cols].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan).dropna(axis=0)\n",
    "    print(\"Model table shape:\", df.shape,\n",
    "          \"| sensors:\", df.index.get_level_values(0).unique().tolist())\n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },
  {
