   "source": [
    "## 8. Features, target, windowing and the LSTM\n",
    "\n",
    "- `X` = all feature columns; `y` = `pm25_ugg_s` (the reference target).\n",
    "- `create_autoregressive_sequences(...)` turns the flat table into overlapping **look-back windows**: each sample is `WINDOW_SIZE` consecutive 15-min rows, and the label is the target at the end of the window.\n",
    "- `build_lstm(...)` defines the network: **LSTM(128) → Dense(64)+LeakyReLU → Dropout(0.3) → Dense(1)**, with L2 regularisation and MSE loss.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hyperparameters (`WINDOW_SIZE=12` ≈ 3 h history, `LEARNING_RATE=1e-4`, `BATCH_SIZE=64`, `EPOCHS=200`) are kept as constants. **Option B must use the same architecture as the saved weights**, so don't change `build_lstm` if you intend to load weights.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "723e3c75",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "WINDOW_SIZE   = 12       # past 15-min steps (~3 hours)\n",
    "LEARNING_RATE = 1e-4\n",
    "BATCH_SIZE    = 64\n",
    "EPOCHS        = 200\n",
    "TARGET        = \"pm25_ugg_s\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def create_autoregressive_sequences(X, y, window):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Build overlapping look-back windows; label = target at the window's end.\"\"\"\n",
    "    Xs, ys = [], []\n",
    "    for i in range(window, len(X)):\n",
    "        Xs.append(X[i - window:i])\n",
    "        ys.append(y[i])\n",
    "    return np.array(Xs), np.array(ys)\n",
    "\n",
    "X = train_df.drop(columns=[TARGET])\n",
    "y = train_df[TARGET]\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_lstm(in_shape, lr=LEARNING_RATE, alpha=0.01, l2_lambda=1e-4):\n",
    "    \"\"\"LSTM(128) -> Dense(64)+LeakyReLU -> Dropout(0.3) -> Dense(1). L2-regularised, MSE.\"\"\"\n",
    "    inp = Input(shape=in_shape)\n",
    "    v = LSTM(128, return_sequences=False, kernel_regularizer=l2(l2_lambda))(inp)\n",
    "    v = Dense(64, kernel_regularizer=l2(l2_lambda))(v)\n",
    "    v = LeakyReLU(alpha=alpha)(v)\n",
    "    v = Dropout(0.3)(v)\n",
    "    out = Dense(1, activation=\"linear\")(v)\n",
    "    model = Model(inp, out, name=\"pm25_lstm\")\n",
    "    model.compile(loss=\"mse\", optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=lr), metrics=[\"mae\"])\n",
    "    return model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1d9c7152",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Scale, window and split (shared by both options)\n",
    "\n",
    "This step is needed for **both** Option A and Option B:\n",
    "- `X_scaler` / `y_scaler` standardise the features and target. They are fit on the whole window, which matches how the saved weights were produced.\n",
    "- the scaled data is turned into look-back sequences,\n",
    "- and split **deterministically** (fixed `SEED`) into **70% train / 20% val / 10% test**, so the loaded-weights path sees exactly the same val/test data the model was evaluated on.\n",
    "\n",
    "`N_FEATURES` is read from the sequences and used to build the network.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "9c58742f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sequences: (32544, 12, 39)\n",
      "Train: (22780, 12, 39)  Val: (6509, 12, 39)  Test: (3255, 12, 39)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X_scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "y_scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_scaled = X_scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "y_scaled = y_scaler.fit_transform(y.values.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()\n",
    "\n",
    "X_seq, y_seq = create_autoregressive_sequences(X_scaled, y_scaled, WINDOW_SIZE)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_temp, X_test_seq, y_temp, y_test_seq = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_seq, y_seq, test_size=0.10, random_state=SEED)\n",
    "X_train_seq, X_val_seq, y_train_seq, y_val_seq = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_temp, y_temp, test_size=0.2222, random_state=SEED)\n",
    "\n",
    "N_FEATURES = X_seq.shape[2]\n",
    "print(\"Sequences:\", X_seq.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Train:\", X_train_seq.shape, \" Val:\", X_val_seq.shape, \" Test:\", X_test_seq.shape)"
   ]
  },
