    "### Option B — Load pretrained weights\n",
    "\n",
    "Skips training. It rebuilds the **same architecture** as `build_lstm` and loads your weights into it. If that file turns out to be a full saved model (`.keras`) instead of a weights file, the cell falls back to `load_model` automatically.\n",
    "\n",
    "Set `WEIGHTS_PATH` to point at your file.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Run this cell **or** the Option A cell, not both.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "8c442703",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Loaded weights into a fresh architecture from pm25_lstm.weights.h5\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "WEIGHTS_PATH = \"pm25_lstm.weights.h5\"   # <-- path to your weights (or a full .keras model)\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    # Most common case: a weights-only file -> rebuild architecture and load weights\n",
    "    model = build_lstm((WINDOW_SIZE, N_FEATURES))\n",
    "    model.load_weights(WEIGHTS_PATH)\n",
    "    print(\"Loaded weights into a fresh architecture from\", WEIGHTS_PATH)\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    # Fallback: the file is a full saved model (.keras / .h5)\n",
    "    print(\"load_weights failed, loading as a full model instead:\", e)\n",
    "    model = tf.keras.models.load_model(WEIGHTS_PATH)\n",
    "    print(\"Loaded full model from\", WEIGHTS_PATH)"
   ]
